At 1:18:03 that the Shuttle never had troubles landing...DEC. 14, 1983 From the Times archive "The space shuttle Columbia was on fire as it landed last Thursday with six crew members and the European Spacelab on board, but the fire and an ensuing explosion were not detected until the next day, officials of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration said today......Steve Nesbitt, a spokesman for the space agency, said the fire occurred in two auxiliary power units. These devices burn a hydrazine fuel to generate electricity to drive the craft's hydraulic system. The hydraulics are used to move flight control surfaces and to deploy the landing gear." More neat stuff in online version: https://www.nytimes.com/1983/12/14/us/fire-and-explosion-on-space-shuttle-went-undetected-in-landing.html.
